name: 1.18.2: Update environment and fix spelling error in German
body:
Bug fixes:
* lib-french-revolutionary-calendar: 1.8.0 -> 1.8.2
https://github.com/caarmen/french-revolutionary-calendar/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md

    1.8.2 (2018-07-04)
    * Update to Kotlin 1.2.51
    * Issue #21: Fix misspelling of german word Wiesenmonat for Prairial.
    1.8.1 (2018-04-01)
    * Fixed VonMadler calculation errors in time zones other than Paris.
    * Fixed Romme calculations after 23:00 in some time zones.

Update environment:
* kotlin: 1.1.51 -> 1.2.51
* support lib: 25.3.1 -> 27.1.1
* android gradle plugin: 2.3.3 -> 3.1.3
* compileSdkVersion: 26 -> 27
* targetSdkVersion: 26 -> 27
* ben-manes: 0.15.0 -> 0.20.0

Remove some unnecessary gradle configuration to "filter resources".

name: 1.18.1: Kotlin
body:
* Rewrote the app in Kotlin.
* Also: Use the roman numeral setting in the converter.

name: 1.18.0 Add Basque translations
body: Also fix the selection of the default font.

name: 1.17.4: Fix spelling of Sansculotides
body: Fixed spelling of Sansculotides, to match the spelling in the [original decree](http://1789-1799.blogspot.fr/2011/12/le-calendrier-republicain-14.html)

name: 1.17.3: Fix Oreo compatibility issues
body:
1.17.3: Fix Oreo compatibility bugs

* Issue 43: Widget stuck in spinner loading animation on Oreo
* Issue 45: Notification not created on Oreo

name: 1.17.1: Two-way converter
body:
Convert both ways, between the revolutionary and Gregorian dates, in the same screen.
This is only for 3.x and higher. Older Android devices will still use the old converter.

name: 1.16.0: Kotlin and font change
body:
* Use the kotlin version of lib-french-revolutionary-calendar
* Replace the OpenSans font by the Roboto font

name: 1.15.1: Fix icon color on widget popup
1.14.0: Removed android wear code
body:
- Google play services is no longer used in this project.
- Removed dependency on the support-compat library.
- There is only the default flavor now (previously there were foss and proprietary flavors).
- The system notification, if enabled, is now sent to wearable devices and the phone.
